    "description": "Ame Kaze Taiyo, Inc. provides food-related services for individuals in Japan. It operates through Services for Individuals and Services for Businesses segments. The company plans, develops, and operates Pocket Marché, an app that allows users to buy fresh seasonal ingredients, such as fruits, vegetables, fish products, and meat products directly from farmers and fishermen; Taberu Times, a monthly food information magazine; and Pokemaru Hometown Tax, a hometown tax payment platform. It also offers Chihokon!, a marriage consultation service that supports local matchmaking; and STAYJAPAN, a hotel reservation website. In addition, the company plans and implements nature study programs for parents and children; and programs, such as local government support services and corporate food ingredient sales. The company was formerly known as Pocket Marche Co., Ltd. and changed its name to Ame Kaze Taiyo, Inc. in April 2022. Ame Kaze Taiyo, Inc. was founded in 2013 and is headquartered in Hanamaki, Japan."
